## Building Your Tracking Infrastructure

The practical question is how to implement effective tracking. Manual approaches involve checking the Polymarket leaderboard regularly, noting top trader wallet addresses, and monitoring their transactions through block explorers. This is tedious and inevitably incomplete. Most traders give up after a few days because the time investment does not scale. Automated approaches using the Polymarket API offer more promise, but building and maintaining such infrastructure requires significant technical skill.

This is exactly the problem that polymarket.tips was designed to solve. The platform continuously monitors the top 50 traders by verified PnL, tracks their positions across all active markets, and surfaces convergence signals when multiple top traders align on the same side. Rather than spending hours on manual tracking or building your own infrastructure, you get a curated feed of the most significant smart money movements. The system also assigns archetype tags to traders based on their historical patterns, helping you understand whether a position comes from a trader who specializes in politics, crypto, or macro events.

Effective tracking also means understanding what you are not seeing. Top traders often build positions gradually to avoid moving markets. They may use multiple wallets or time their entries around liquidity events. A good Polymarket tracker accounts for these patterns rather than simply reporting raw transactions. The goal is actionable intelligence, not data overload.

